I replied saying it was sad her mother was an entitled bitch and couldn't respect what flowers her own daughter wanted for her wedding day.
Literally and I'm not even joking, literally two hours later, my beautiful bride from today (April 1st) emailed me saying, she knows it's late notice but was there anyway I was available, as her florist had just cancelled on her due to unforeseen circumstances.
Karina my love, you and I and April first, were meant to be together

social_posts.post_text:
Frannie traveling crown series is back and kicking off with this tear jerker. When I was traveling Europe solo for 2019 I started creating crowns for people who stole a piece of my heart. This is Tom and he has taken the whole damn thing 💔
My house husband but so so so damn much more. I don't know how to summarize my love for you Tom. Except that when you fly to London on Tuesday, I'm gonna ball my fucking eyes out.
One, because you've been the most incredibly safe fortress of healing and growth, for me and my rescue grey baby. That the fun we have everyday together, is over for now. That we won't laugh till we choke at dumb shit, high as larks on our couch anymore. That I'm losing my best bud who I rave with, cry with, cook with, ponder in the dog park with, afternoon swim with, live in perfection with, host legendary dinner parties with. It's all beautiful memories like the time you dressed as a farmers daughter for the harvest moon
But two because I'm so proud of you, of who you're becoming, of all you've done and everyone on the other side of the world who now gets to love you too. Your heart is generous and void of judgement. Your hugs are tight and long. Your laugh lights up a room. Your passion for teaching the next generation is irreplaceable. You're one of a kind and the best kind. I often think about how much more incredible the earth would be if everyone had a best friend like Tom. How seen we would all feel. How comfortable we would be to grow and learn and feel. How much fun we'd have. 
You've taught me so much about love and relationships and general well being. I feel indebted to you for all the free therapy.  I'm unbelievably fortunate to have met and loved you. I love you Tom. Now fly free, onto the next adventure you're so deserving of having. It's going to be as incredible as you are, I just know it xxx all my love, Frannie + Mari
#frannietravellingblooms

I think the warm salty tears are done rolling down my cheeks and I can give myself a gold star on grieving, move on with my life and welcome new love into my heart, but they aren't done and the smallest things let alone everything reminds me of you and so the tears don't stop pouring.
Platonic love in the most intimate and affectionate of ways with some rando I met off Facebook house mates. I said to him, as we hugged each other tight for like the 8th last time, "I didn't even know you three years ago!" Trying to convince my feelings to chill with the feels. But my future has been shaped now by your kindness, your patience, your humanness. It's pretty hard to hide who you actually are when you live together and Tom and I trauma bonded fairly quickly. I think my overshare about an encounter with a micro penis, disarmed all efforts of secrecy between us and from there we've made our home a space to burst into tears mid sentence, question misconceptions and intentions with open mindedness and empathy. The home of our friendship a place to explore things together that before had poor connotations, now the most precious of memories. Tom has raised the bar of love I desire in my life. High enough it's blatantly apparent to me, those who don't meet my needs, apparent enough to end a goodish thing with someone I'd been seeing since Jan because I know my worth and no one can make me question the love i deserve, like the love Tom showed me for two and a bit years. Love that's forgiving and all encompassing, love that's honest and courageous enough to speak honestly. Love where you're strong one moment but broken the next and thats perfectly okay. 
I want to encourage everyone to make opportunities to find connection with others because if you have your narrative already engraved, there is no space for things that are even better than you can conceive. Things like a Tom and I kinda love. And I would rather have loved and lost that Tom kinda love, in a proximity convenience way at least, than to never have had the most incredible years of my life with a new dear friend who I will love forever. I love you Tom 
Londoners, reach out and take care of my mate pretty please 🙏🥺

Life really isn't A. to B.
Yet we're sold that narrative and we hold our breath in-between, wasting majority of our precious time, idealizing that finish line, that gold star, that completion satisfaction.
It's bullshit, take a breath, enjoy the ride

You're going to have to bare with me here, I'm feeling quite philosophical. 
Long story short, the past month has been an emotional one and as low as the lows have been felt with streaming tears, the highs brilliant ecstasy, a welcome relief. 
I've been in therapy for the past 4 and a bit years, not as often as I possibly should have but as much as I could muster and I would argue that's the perfect amount. 
It's so wonderful to feel things changing within me on a cellular level. The tireless work finally paying off. Like how I bought these tulips that were supposed to be white... Old me would have ruminated on the injustice, the audacity, the ludicrousy, the Idiocracy and failing of me, a so called professional, making this mistake, what a fool, what an imposter! 
New me put them on my dining table and enjoyed the unintended gift I bestowed upon myself. End story.
And this might seem incomprehensible to you, you might live your life free of anxiety and over thinking, if you do, you're luckier than you'll ever know and sometimes I lust for that ignorant existence. 
But me, I genetically pull everything apart to make sense of it. Words, interactions, actions, behaviors, colours, intentions, meaningless gestures, craft, basically just the entirety of my reality and golly gosh that shits exhausting. 
Therapy
Get therapy
It really really really helps
Also tulips, get tulips, regardless of the colour, they help too

I think about this most days and the days I forget, someone reminds me

Reasons to have an indoor ceremony
1. Cosy AF
2. No need to worry about weather
3. Dress won't get ruined on grass/mud
4. Even floor surface unlike outside so you have less chance of falling down the aisle
5. Controllable lighting for photography
6. NO WIND!
7. Allows your vendors to set up a little earlier because they're not worried about the weather too
8. Building backdrop better for photos
9. It's warm and your guests won't freeze
10. Flowers last longer because they haven't been butt raped by the sun

Happiest 60th birthday to my mum
The thought that you were almost taken away from me when I was 11, completely out of your control, scans lit up like a Christmas tree, told you had months left to live, BUT you defied the odds, left modern science puzzled and got to be my mum for another two decades and counting. 
I will NEVER get over how fortunate I am to have you still. 
I am literally non-existent without you.

Everything I am, everything I create is because of you. 
You made my hands, my heart, my head. 

I love you with all my heart

Ten years ago today I got married
And to put it lightly, ALOT has happened since then
Being a florist who creates wedding florals, simultaneously processing my own heart shattering grief surrounding the so called failure of my investments in somebody else, for what had seemed like a lifetime, has been an interesting ride to stay the very least. 
The only thing I regret of those 12 years partnered is that I didn't know my own value because EVERYTHING is consequential of that fact 

Did I look and feel like a million bucks on my wedding day?
You betcha!
Do I demonized my open and generous heart?
Absolutely not!
Have I forgiven myself? 
Almost, don't worry, I'm working on it

I will keep loving wholeheartedly and smiling ear to ear for all my days
AND
I LOVE that i haven't yet met everybody who is going to love me in this lifetime 
If anything, my idea of love has evolved and transformed so much so, that there is an unbelievable and unmeasurable amount of love in my life. A type of love I couldn't conceive of ever feeling whilst being married 
And what feels like the end of the world, will in time, fade to be just a memory.
I'll keep on living, now knowing my value and standing firm in what I believe I deserve

Your silence is deafening.
I honestly would have bet my life on your courage and then you've clearly displayed, you have none
I don't know how to even remain open to those in my life who have said nothing, shared nothing, signed nothing, done nothing. 
Are you proud of who you are, that when atrocities occur, your privilege to ignore, for your comfort takes precedence? 
Your "feelings" over others existence, takes precedence!
We've been conditioned to assume our comfort is paramount, that our feeling are useless to create change
So when you're comfortable tomorrow, in safety, in delusion, opening gifts, sharing nourishment, I hope you're haunted by your privilege, I hope your pleasure is eternally unsatisfactory. 
I'm furious, I'm destroyed, I'm hopeless but at least I'm feeling
At least I'm saying, sharing, signing, doing all I can. 
Christmas is cancelled in Bethlehem but go ahead and drink the Koolaid. I doubt it makes you feel better 
💔

FORGET about keeping up with the beige Jones's 
CHOOSE colour to express your wedding day delight
Every event I've created with vibrant luscious tonal deliciousness has stopped guests in their tracks! 
It evokes joy and wonder and what better feelings to hold you in your celebration of LOVE
BLESS @keegancronin for not only capturing this wedding in all it's petally glory but being skilled enough to edit in a true to life colour scheme! God I love a highly skilled photographer!

"I promise to say I love you every single day and in three different languages"
I'm pretty desensitized to wedding vows these days as I have probably been at almost 1000 ceremonies but when I heard Christina speak these precious words to Eric, I actually burst into tears, funnily enough, I'm just behind that stone wall, eavesdropping.
This utterly gorgeous couple had no idea what was in store for them as briefly after their stunning wedding nuptials Eric was diagnosed with an aggressive cancer and given a terrible prognosis. 3 years later they are still fighting it and flying all across the world to treat it. They have a precious baby boy and they deserve every single happiness in all of the universe
They are just about to embark on a new adventure relocating to Paris so they can be closer to treatment in Germany. 
I would love to support them in any way possible through you my beautiful followers, whether you are able to donate to the GoFundMe for Eric's treatment or if you have any connections in Paris so they can be welcomed and find community. I have a link in my bio to Christina's update for all the details on GoFundMe
Surely out of all of my followers and especially after creating wedding florals in Paris itself, I have connections in Paris to assist this beautiful couples transition to the other side of the world.
